  "prompt": "What are some places to visit enroute Chennai to Pondicherry?",
  "response": "Traveling from Chennai to Pondicherry offers a variety of interesting and picturesque places you can visit along the way. Here are some notable spots:\n\n1. **Mahabalipuram (Mamallapuram)**: This UNESCO World Heritage site is known for its ancient rock-cut temples, sculptures, and monuments. Key attractions include the Shore Temple, Arjuna\u2019s Penance, and the Pancha Rathas (Five Rathas).\n\n2. **Covelong Beach (Kovalam Beach)**: Located near Chennai, this beach is ideal for relaxation and offers water sports like windsurfing and swimming. There's also a fort and a Catholic church you can explore.\n\n3. **Muttukadu**: This backwater area offers boating and rowing facilities. It's a peaceful spot to enjoy the scenic beauty and participate in water sports.\n\n4. **Tiger Cave**: Near Mahabalipuram, this less-crowded location features sculpted rocks and is believed to have been an open-air theater.\n\n5. **Auroville**: Although closer to Pondicherry, Auroville is worth a stop. It's an experimental township aimed at human unity, with attractions like the Matrimandir and beautiful gardens.\n\n6. **Sadras Fort**: This historical Dutch fort is less known but offers a fascinating glimpse into colonial architecture and history.\n\n7. **Mudaliarkuppam**: This is another boating site located on the East Coast Road, where you can enjoy boat rides in the serene waters.\n\n8. **Chunnambar Boat House**: Located just before Pondicherry, it's a lovely spot for boating and picnics. You can take a boat ride to Paradise Beach, which is known for its pristine beauty.\n\nDriving along the East Coast Road (ECR) will provide you with scenic views of the Bay of Bengal and several small pretty beaches where you can stop and enjoy the seaside atmosphere.\n\nMake sure to check the timings and accessibility of these places as you plan your trip. Enjoy your journey from Chennai to Pondicherry!",
